A chopper carrying Isiolo governor Muhammed Kuti and three others made an emergency landing in Mukurwe-ini, Nyeri County due to bad weather. The helicopter crash-landed at Kiangoma village near Mukurwe-ini Boys High School on Friday morning. According to an eye witness Patrick Githinji, the chopper was seen hovering at the same area before landing. "It was about 10:30 am when we saw the chopper flying around the same area. The pilot was looking for somewhere to land before landing in someone's farm," he said. It grounded in a maize, arrowroots and maize farm. The chopper, he said stayed for about an hour and took off after the weather improved. However, he said, they could not immediately establish where the governor was heading to. Click here for the latest political news